{"key":"processedPost-7350831","value":{"id":7350831,"first":7334981,"last":7369486,"when":1188478159,"utime":"08/30/07 03:49 PM","content":"Never heat a terrarium.  The temperature differential will 'steal' your humidity in order to turn it into condensation on the walls-bad idea.<br /><br />You want upper ninety percent humidity inside your terrarium.  Rinsed and well drained perlite is an excellent way to get this.  Use a small heater in the room to get the temps to upper sixties-low seventies and you'll be fine.<br />RR","title":"Re: Opinions needed on my first Terrarium"}}